快速註冊



臺大“建築史與都市史”書單


暖雪
2009-06-18 19:13:13




Graduate Institute of Building and Planning	Spring 2009National Taiwan University	C.J.Hsia----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------COURSE SYLLABUS544-D0840: RESEARCH METHODS: ARCHITECTURAL HISTORY AND CRITICISM研究方法：建築史與建築批評3 units 建築與城鄉研究所，公館101星期一 下午6,7,8（14:20-17:20 p.m.）I. Description of the CourseThis is a year-long seminar primarily geared to PhD students in the option of architectural and urban history. We will review the growth, aims, tools, and methods of architectural and urban history. Our subject matter, then, is the literature of our field; critical concepts like architectural styles, morality in architecture, Zeitgeist, architecture as cultural expression, and architecture as the symbolic expression of the urban meaning through social historical process of the structure; the identity of important historians and the schools they represent; the relation of architectural history to the practice, theory and criticism of architecture, and to allied disciplines like archaeology, sociology, anthropology, urban geography and art history etc. This semester is largely investigative and theoretical on architectural history. In the next semester we will focus on the theories and methods of urban history.　　這是個兩學期的課程，主要提供為有關建築史與都市史的博士班學生之方法論方面的討論課程。我們將討論建築史與都市史之成長、目標、工具與研究方法。主要內容包括這領域的主要文獻、主要概念（像建築風格、建築中的道德規範、時代精神、建築為文化的表現、社會結構之歷史過程的都市意義的表現）、重要史學及其代表之學派、建築史與實踐之關係、建築之理論與批評，以及相關的諸學域如考古學、社會學、人類系、都市地理學與藝術史等。上學期大部分集中於建築史的理論與調查，下學期則集中於都市史的理論與方法。II. Outline of the Course        1. Introduction: The History of Architectural History        2. What is Architectural History?        3. Basic Documents of Architectural History        4. Reconstruction and Restoration        5. Methods of Architectural History:         (1). The Aesthetic/ Formalist Approach,a. Styleb. Space; Einfuhlung (empathy)c. Typology (architectonics)d. Applications        (2). The Technology and Structural/ Moral Approach        (3). The Social Cultural Approach        (4). The Critical Approach         (5). Iconography, Symbolism, Semiotics        6. Theory, History and CriticismIII. Assignments for the Students1. Regular attendance;2. Extensive reading;3. Term paper: a book-review article.IV. Textbooks1. Porphyrios, Demetri, ed., Methodology of Architectural History, London: Architectural Design, 1981.2. Ockman, Joan, et al. ed., Architecture Criticism Ideology, Princeton, N.J.: Princeton Architectural Press, 1985.3. Ockman, Joan, et al. ed., Architecture Reproduction, Princeton, N.J.: Princeton Architectural Press, 1988.4. Tafuri, Manfredo, The Sphere and the Labyrinth, The MIT Press, 1990. 0. Preliminary Reading（課前準備）          夏鑄九，1993，“營造學社—梁思成建築史論述構造之理論分析”，《空間，歷史與社會》，臺北：台灣社會研究叢刊—03，頁1-49。        卡爾‧馬克斯，1852，“路易‧波拿巴的霧月十八日”，《馬克斯恩格斯選集》，第一卷，北京：人民出版社，1994，頁：579-670。(註意文中對階級意識與農民問題的處理。)        Hobsbawm, E., On History, London: New Press, 1998.（有中譯）        Jenkins, K., Re-thinking History, London: Routledge, 1991.（有中譯）   Jenkins, K., On 'What is History?', London: Routledge, 1995. （有中譯）   Preziosi, D., Rethinking Art History, New Haven: Yale University Press, 1989.------------------------I. Introduction: The History of Architectural History 導論：建築史的歷史    The remarks deal with a broad background. They should be supplemented by specific accounts of historiography, esp.*  Watkin, D., The Rise of Architectural History, London, 1980.   Liang, A.K. and E.C. Rae, "The Founding and First Years of the Society of Architectural Historians from 1940", JSAH, Vol.XLIX, No.7-8, March 1990, pp.7-8.   Overby, O., "From 1947: The Society of Architectural Historians", JSAH, Vol.XLIX, No.7-8, March 1990, pp.9-14.   Maass, J., "Where Architectural Historians Fear to Tread", Society of Architectural Historian, Vol.XXVIII, No.1, March 1969.   Poppeliers, J.C., "Historiographic Development in the History of Architecture", Catholic University of America Dissertation, Washington DC 1975.        Hsia, Chu-joe, 2002, 10, “The Paradigm Shift in the Education of Architecture and Planning in the Global Information Age”, Keynote Speech Paper for 2002 Seoul International Conference on East Asian Architectural History - Traditional Architecture in modern Asia (TAmA), The Korean Association of Architectural History, Seoul, October 17-19, 2002.夏鑄九，2004，12，“關於歷史與理論：研究與教學”，設計研究的回顧與前瞻研討會，設計史論專題部分主持人論文，國科會人文處藝術學門主辦，雲林科技大學承辦，2004年12月18日。初步認識建築史本身論述的歷史形構(the historical formation of the discourse of architectural history)是本週的主題，建議試著由建築史的角度思考更貼身的困境：現代建築是在什麼脈絡下在近代亞洲建構的？以及，面對當前的全球資訊化趨勢下建築與規劃教育的範型轉移，亞洲的建築教育，以至於建築史教育要如何因應？然後，由下週開始建築史論述實踐中的抵抗與反省軌跡。 II. What is Architectural History?        什麼是建築史？*  Wright, G., and J. Parks, eds. The History of History in American Schools of Architecture 1865-1975, Princeton: Princeton Architectural Press, 1990. *  Kubler, G., The Shape of Time, New Haven, 1962.   Kubler, G., "What Can Historians do for Architecture?", in Perspecta, 9/10, 1965, pp.299-302.   Kubler, G., "The Shape of Time Reconsidered", Perspecta, No.19, 1982, pp.112-121.   Whiffen, M.m ed. The History, Theory and Criticism of Architecture, Cambridge, Mass.: The MIT Press, 1970.   Hancock, J.E., ed. History in of and for Architecture, Cincinnati, 1981. ---------------------   Collins, P., Changing Ideals in Modern Architecture, Montreal 1965.*  Allsopp, B., The Study of Architectural History, New York, 1970.（註：書中所提希羅多德(Herodotus)的歷史(Historiae)已有中譯，王以鑄譯，臺北：台灣商務。）   Conway, H., and R. Roenisch, Understanding Architecture: An Introduction to Architecture and Architectural History, London: Routledge, 1994. (ch.3)Arnold, Dana, Reading Architectural History, London: Routledge 2002. (Ch.1)*  Porphyrios, D., ed. On the Methodology of Architectural History, London, 1981.(pp.2, 3-10, 61-68, 96-104)    *  Tafuri, M., Theories and History of Architecture, London, 1980. (Italian Original 1976)   La storia dell'architettura, problemi di metodo e di didattica, Atti del convegno nazionale 1974, published by the Istituto di storia dell'architettura dell'Universita degli studi Firenze in 1976.   The discussion will consider the relation of architectural history and the general discipline of history, the traditional practices and goals of architectural historians, the present state and future thrusts of the field. This is by way of introduction to the more detailed study of schools of architectural history which will engage us in subsequent weeks.首先，看看美國的建築學院的歷史，以及，建築史教育與建築教育的關係與自主性的建構，我們以耶魯建築史為例，看看Kubler的考古學知識角色。最後，看看建築史本身的論述內容，以及緊接著，在1970年代社會動力下學院的建築史家的反思。王敏穎，“建築史在西方與中國專業學院中的定位——從十八世紀迄今”（Architectural History in Western and Chinese Professional Schools: from the Eighteenth Century to the Present），《台灣大學建築與城鄉研究所學報》。（即將出版） III. Basic Documents of Architectural History    建築史的基本文獻   Based on a case study, we will discuss the visual and literary documents from which architectural history is composed. The list includes: the building fabric itself; primary documents such as drawings, models, contracts, commemorative medals, letters, inscriptions; secondary documents such as travel accounts, vedute, manuals of iconography. *  Kostof, S., ed. The Architect: Chapters in the History of the Profession, New York, 1977.   Wilton-Ely, J., "The Architectural Model: English Baroque", Apollo, No.88, 1968.   Narjoux, F., Monuments eleves par la ville de Paris de 1985 a 1880, Paris, 1877-81; and Haussmann, E., Memories, Paris 1890.   Kuthmann, H., et al., Bauten Roms auf Munzen und Medaillen, Munich, 1973; and a related volume, Donaldson, T.L., Architectura numismatica; or, Architectural Medals of Classical Antique, London, 1895.   Bloch, H.I., bolli laterrizi e la storia edilizia romana, Rome 1947: the classic study of Roma brick stamps.   Hyman, Isabelle, Fifteenth Century Florentine Studies: The Palazzo Medici and A Ledger for the Church of San Lorenzo, New York, 1977.   Bundgaard, J.A., Mnesicles, A Greek Architect at Work, Copenhagen 1957: building inscriptions concerning the Telesterion at Eleusis and the Arsenal at Piraeus.   Peroni, ed., Annli della fabbrica del Duomo di Milano, Milan 1877-85; reprinted 1979.        Arnold, Dana, Reading Architectural History, London: Routledge 2002. (Ch.2)        楊鴻勛，《建築考古學論文集》，北京：文物出版社，1987。        劉敘傑主編，《中國古代建築史》，第一卷，北京：中國建築工業出版社，2003。        劉敘傑等，《中國古代建築》，臺北：木馬，2003。（繁體字版） IV. Reconstruction and Restoration         重建與修復   The recreation of architectural reality on the basis of literary descriptions, conceptual drawings, and material remains. Individual reports will focus on one famous instance and review the issues involved, the history of the problem, the nature of the results.   Horn, W., and E. Born, The Plan of St. Gall, 3 vols, Berkeley, 1979.   O'Gorman,J., Henry Hobson Richarson and His Office, Boston, 1975; and O'Gorman's article in the JSAH, No.37, Oct. 1978, pp.175-194: Richardson's Marshall Field Store in Chicago.      Downey, G., "On Some Post-Classical Architectural Terms", Transactions of the American Philological Association, No.77, 1946, pp.22-34. ( problems presented by architectural terms in literary texts)*  To this discussion belongs also the thorny issue of architectural restoration: Knossos, Ostia, Pompeii, Williamsburg. You might look up the entry on "Restoration" in The Encyclopedia of World Art: the issue of architectural restoration on Knossos, Osttia, Pompeii, Williamsburg, etc. and thinking of Evans, Viollet-le-Duc, even the Getty Museum.閱讀：陳志梧，1988，“空間變遷的社會歷史分析：以日本殖民時期的宜蘭地景為個案”，台灣大學土木研究所博士論文。（特別註意附錄，清葛瑪蘭成的復原）閱讀：楊鴻勛，1987，《建築考古學論文集》，北京：文物出版社。      楊鴻勛，1997，“唐長安大明宮含元殿復原再論”， 《城市與設計》，第一期，6月，頁75-102。傅熹年，1973，“唐長安大明宮含元殿復原的探討”， 《文物》，第七期。傅熹年，1998，《傅熹年建築史論文集》，北京：文物出版社。 V. Methods of Architectural History:   1. The Aesthetic/ Formalist Approach   (1). Style建築史方法：1.	美學/形式主義取向(1). 風格*  Lang, Berel, eds. The Concept of Style, 1979.*  Ackerman, J.S., “Style”, Art and Archaeology, 1963, pp.164- 186. ( and “Postscript”, 1991) *  Gombrich, E.H., entry on Style in The International Encyclopedia of the Social Sciences.*  Schapiro, M., “Style”, Anthropology Today, A.L. Kroeber ed., 1953, pp.287-312; reprinted in Aesthetic Today, M. Philipson ed., 1961, pp.81-113.*  Frankl, P., “The ‘Crazy’ Vaults of Lincoln Cathedral” Art Bulletin, No.35, 1953, pp.95-108: good methodological arguments against a determinist development of style. Ref.:Frankl's textbook and Kostof's article on Frankl:   Frankl, P., Principles of Architectural History, first published as Die Entwicklungphasen der neueren Baukunst. First English translation, 1932.             Kostof, S., “Paul Frankl's Principles of Architectural History”, in Porphirios, D., ed., On the Methodology of Architectural History, 1981, pp.21-24.----------------------   Seminal texts:*  Wolffin, H., Principles of Art History, 1932. (German Original 1915).*  Facillon, H., Vie des formes, 1934, translated as The Life Form in Art, New York, 1942, by Hogan and Kubler.   You should also be aware of Wolfflin's predecessors and contemporaries, e.g. Adolf Goller (Entstehung der architectonischen Stilformen, 1888, or the slightly earlier Zur Aesthetik der Architektur), Gottfried Semper, the great Alois Riegl (Stilfragen, 1893), or the so called "formalist" school of art history Emil Kaufmann who remains untranslateded into English. ref.:   Rkywert, J., “Gottfroed Semper and the Problem of Style”,   Quintavalle, A.C., "The Philosophical Context of Riegl's Stilfragen",   Teyssot, G., "Neoclassic and 'Autonomous' Architecture: The Formalism of Emil Kaufmann". -----------------------------   Hubsch, Heinrich, et al., In What Style Should we Build?: The German Debate on Architectural Style, 1992.   Poppeliers, J. et al., What Style Is It?, 1976. ---------------------------   And there is a lot of recent material you ought to be familiar with, e.g. Finch, M., Style in Art History, 1974; or the recent reformulation of the formalist approach by Arnkeim, R., The Dynamics of Architectural Form, Berkeley, 1977; compare also with:*  Twombly, R., Power and Style: A Critique of Twentieth- Century Architecture in the United States, New York: Hill and Wang, 1995.*  Hebdige, D., Subculture: The Meaning of Style, London, 1979.先認識建築史論述中對風格的界定，什麼是風格？以及，是在甚麼脈絡下定義風格？然後，以二十世紀美國建築為例，思考風格與權力的關係，更進一步，在認識論層次上，比較文化研究中對風格的不同界定並做進一討論！ V. Methods of Architectural History:   1. The Aesthetic/ Formalist Approach   (2). Space; Einfuhlung (empathy)建築史方法：1.	美學/形式主義取向(2). 空間，神入*  Zevi, B., Architecture as Space, 1957; see also his entry on "Architecture" in the Encyckopedia of World Art. *  Scott, G., The Architecture of Humanism, first pub. 1924.   Additional references:    Van de Venm C.J.M., "Concerning the Idea of Space: The Rise of A New Fundamental in German Architectural Theory and in the Modern Movement until 1930", Univ. of Pennsylvania dissertation 1974.*  Zucker, P., "The Paradox of Architectural Theories at the Beginning of the Modern Movement", JSAH, V.10, N.3, 1951, pp.8- 14.   Lipps, Theodor, Raumaesthetik und geometrisch-optische Tauschungen, 1897; Scott's predecessor.   Scruton, R., The Aesthetics of Architecture, Princeton 1979.   Norberg-Schulz, C., Existence, Space and Architecture, 1971.   Baird, G., The Space of Appearance, 1995.   Etlin, R.A. Symbolic Space: French Enlightenment Architecture and Its Legacy, 1994.---------------------*  See also the entries on "production of space", "space", "spatial structure", and "spatiality" in The Dictionary of Human Geography, 4th Edition, 2000.*  Sack, R.D., Conceptions of Space in Social Thought: A Geographic Perspective, 1980.*  Buttimer, A., and D. Seaman, The Human Experience of Space and Place, 1980.*  Tuan, Y.F., Space and Place, 1974.*  Lefebvre, Henri, Production of Space, Oxford: Blackwell, 1991.先認識建築史論述中對空間的界定，什麼是空間？以及，是在甚麼脈絡下定義空間？然後，比較地理學、現象學或是新人文地理學、以及社會理論對空間的理論建構，註意空間生產、空間、空間結構與空間性的概念界定。 V. Methods of Architectural History:   1. The Aesthetic/ Formalist Approach,   (3). Typology (Architectonics)建築史方法：1.	美學/形式主義取向(3). 類型學*  Argan, G.C., "Typology", Enciclopedia U