. 應用Select an architectural style, and report on the following: What are the characteristics of the style? who formulated them? how useful or successful has this designation proved? Remember this is historiography. We are concerned with the making of styles by historians.        examples:        Neoclassicism: see H. Honour's book of that name, 1968.        Roman vaulted style: see W. MacDonald, The Architecture of Roman Empire, 1965 and new revised ed.' also see his new book: Hadrian's Villa and Its Legacy, 1995.        Shingle style' stick style: see V. Scully.        International Style: see the 1932 Hitchcock/Johnson book.        Post-modernism:        Jencks, J., The Language of Post-Modern Architecture, 3d ed., 1981.        MacLeod, M., "Architecture and Politics in the Regain Era: From Postmodernism to Deconstructivism", Assemblage, No.8, Feb. 1989, pp.222-59.        Others: new Brutalism, art-deco, Federal, Victorian Gothic, Ottonian, Hellenistic, Romanesque...--------------------        Arnold, Dana, Reading Architectural History, London: Routledge 2002. (Ch.5)        Bourdieu, Pierre, Distinction: A Social Critique of the Judgement of Taste, Cambridge, Mass.: Harvard University Press, 1984.        Vale, L., Architecture, Power and National Identity. 1992.        認識建築史家應用建築風格的研究成果，最後，比較社會學者與近年社會理論影響下對風格的社會批判角度。 V. Methods of Architectural History:      2. Technology and Structural/ Moral Approach建築史方法：2.	技術與結構的/倫理的取向*	Watkin, D., Morality and Architecture, 1977.        Viollet-le-Duc, E.E., Historire de L'architectur, 1863-72.        Auguste Choisy, Histoire de L'architecture, Paris, 1899.        Abraham, P., Violet-le-Duc et rationalism medieval, Paris 1934.        Banham, R., The Architecture of the Well-Tempered Environment, 1969.        Banham, R., Theory and Design in the First Machine Age, 1960.        Giedion, G., Mechanization Takes Command, 1948.        Pevsner, N., Ruskin and Viollet-le-Duc, London, 1969: and Pioneers of Modern Design, first published in 1936 and Pioneers of the Modern Movement from William Morris to Walter Gropius.        Abraham, P., Experiments in Gothic Structure, MIT 1982.認識現代建築運動影響下建築史學所未自覺的，對結構技術的規範性偏見；英國保守主義右翼學者大衛‧華金(David Watkin)的犀利批判特別值得註意。 V. Methods of Architectural History:      3. The Social Cultural Approach        建築史方法：3.	社會文化取向        Hauser, A., The Social History of Art, 1951.        Hauser, A., Mannerism: The Crisis of the Renaissance and the Origin of Modern Art, 1965.        Hauser, A., The Sociology of Art, 1982. (G. Origin 1974)        Hauser, A., The Philosophy of Art, 1958.        M., Girouard's books: The Victorian Country House, 1971; Sweetness and Light, 1977; Life in the English Country House, 1978; Aweetness and Light, 1977.        Arnold, Dana, Reading Architectural History, London: Routledge 2002. (Ch.4)(將Girouard與Grombrich並列)        Goldthwaite, R.A., The Building of Renaissance Florence: A Social and Economic History, 1981.        Vanelli, V., Economic dell' architecture in Roma liberale.        Mathews, T.F., The Early Churches of Constantinople, 1971.        Kostof, S., "Do Buildings Lie?".[Cultural Geography]        Knapp, Ronald, “Asia’s Diversity & Asia’s Dwellings: A Geographer’s Perspective”, paper presented in 2002 Seoul International Conference on East Asian Architectural History - Traditional Architecture in modern Asia (TAmA), The Korean Association of Architectural History, Seoul, October 17-19, 2002.        Knapp, Ronald, China’s Traditional Rural Architecture, 1986; The Chinese House, 1990; Chinese Landscapes: The Village as Place, 1992; China’s Walled Cities, 2000; China’s Old Dwellings, 2000; Asia’s Old Dwellings, 2003.這是建築史與藝術史的重要知識傳統之一，值得多閱讀並討論它們與文化地理學者共享的某些人文主義的共同遺產，羅納‧那普(Roland Knapp)的中國民居研究是一個需要做理論比較的好例子。 V. Methods of Architectural History:4.	Iconography, Symbolism, Semiotics建築史方法：4. 圖象學，象徵論，記號學        Panofsky, E., Studies in Iconology, 1939.        Panofsky, E., Meaning in the Visual Art, 1955.        Panofsky, E., Gothic Architecture and Scholasticism, 1951.        Panofsky, E., Idea: A Concept in Art Theory, 1968.        Panofsky, E., Perspective as Symbolic Form, 1991.        Holly, M.A., Panofsky and the Foundations of Art History, 1984.        Jencks, C., and G. Baird, eds. Meaning in Architecture, 1969.        Hautecoeur, L., Mystique et architecture, symbolism of du cercle et de la coupole, 1954.        Baldwin, Smith E., Architectural Symbolism of Imperial Rome and the Middle Ages, 1956' The Dome, A Study in the History of Ideas, 1950.        Krautheimer, R., “Introduction to an Iconography of Medieval Architecture”, Journal of Warburg and Courtauld, No.5, 1942, pp.1-34; reprinted with postscript in Krautheimer, Studies in Early Christian, Medieval and Renaissance Art, 1969, pp.115-150.        Grabar, A., Martyrium, Paris, 1946.        Hersey, G.L., High Victorian Gothic, A Study in Associations特別註意藝術史的重要知識傳統，華堡學派厄文‧潘諾夫斯基(Erwin Panofsky)對形式的特殊性分析的貢獻。 V. Methods of Architectural History:5.	The Critical Approach建築史方法：5. 批判取向        Hadjinicolaou, N., Art History and Class Struggle, 1978.        Hadjinicolaou, N., “Art History and the History of the Appreciation of Works of Art”, 1978        Hadjinicolaou, N., “On the Ideology of Avant-gardism”, 1982.        Hadjinicolaou, N., “Disarming 1830:  A Parisian Counter Revolution”, 1981.Arnold, Dana, Reading Architectural History, London: Routledge 2002. (Ch.3)（將Hadjinicolaou與Summerson並列）        Clark, T.J., The Absolute Bourgeois:  Artists and Politics in France, 1848-1851, 1973.        Clark, T.J., Image of the People:  Gustave Courbet and the 1848 Revolution, 1973.        Clark, T.J., The Painting of Modern Life:  Paris in the Art of Manet and His Followers, 1984.        Tafuri, M., The Sphere and Labyrinth 1987.  "The Historical Project", 1979.        Tafuri, M., Architecture and Utopia, 1975.        Tafuri, M., and F. Dal Co., Modern Architecture, 1979.        Tafuri, M., History of Italian Architecture, 1944-1985, 1989.        Tafuri, M. Interpreting the Renaissance: Princes, Cities, Architects, 2006.       Tafuri, M. and Leach A. Manfredo Tafuri: Choosing History, 2008.         “Interview:  Manfredo Tafuri”, Transition, Vol.2, No.3/4, 1981.        Lipstadt, Helene, and Harvey Mendelsohn, "Philosophy, History, and Autobiography:  Manfredo Tafuri and the 'Unsurpassed Lesson' of Le Corbusier", Assemblage, No.22, Dec. 1993, 58-103.        Porphrios, Demetri, Sources of Modern Eclecticism, 1982.        Cacciari, Massimo, Architecture and Nihilism: On the Philosophy of Modern Architecture, 1993.        Wigley, Mark, The Architecture of Deconstruction:  Derrida's Haunt, 1993.        Benedikt, Michael, Deconstructing the Kimbell, 1991.        Ockman, Joan et al., eds. Architecture Criticism Ideology, 1985.        Ockman, Joan et al., eds. Architecture production, 1988.for the second category : the Historian and Politics        Millon, H.A,  “The Role of History of Architecture in Fascist Italy”, JSAH, No.24, Jan. 1965.        Nochlin/Millon, eds. Art and Architecture in the Service of Politics 1978, papers by Stapleford, Westfall, von Moos, Searing, Kostof.        Miller Lane, B., Architecture and Politics in Germeny, 1918-1945, 1968.        Kostof, S., The Third Rome, 1973.        Kopp, A., Town and Revolution, Soviet Architecture and City Planning, 1917-1935, 1970. (Original pub. in French in 1967)        von Simson, O., Sacred Fortress, Byzantine Art and Stratecraft in Ravanna, 1948.        Doordan, D.P., “The Political Content in Italian Architecture during the Fascist Era”, Art Journal, Summer 1983, pp.121-131.主要是1970年代社會運動衝擊下新馬克斯主義對建築史學的影響，以及，建築史研究中對政治議題的爭議，值得討論它對政治向來採取不發言的社會與知識的脈絡。要有能力區分庸俗馬克斯主義與馬克斯主義的影響，尤其是馬克斯主義對史學的價值。註意對空間-社會轉化過程的歷史動態（力）分析，如何可以補社會科學之不足，形成對社會科學的批判。最後，做為歷史研究方法，馬克斯主義取向做為討論“現代”的起點，其方法論上的優勢值得留意。5.1	Microhistory5.1	微觀史學由於Manfredo Tufuri的原因，我們在這一部份可以延伸到義大利微觀史學，以Carlo Ginzburg為代表的史家，對農民與工匠手藝人的細微線索的探究：李尚仁，“如何書寫被排除者的歷史——金士伯格論傅柯的瘋狂使研究”，《科技、醫療與社會》，第三期，2005年3月，頁：157-227。傅柯，《古典時代瘋狂史》，臺北：時報，1998。（林志明中譯）Ginzburg, C., The Night Battles, 1983. （有中譯）Ginzburg, C. and R. Rosenthal, Ecstasies: Deciphering the Witches’ Sabbath, 1991.Ginzburg, C. et al., The Cheese and the Worms, 1992.Ginzburg, C. et al., Clues, Myths, and the Historical Method, 1992.Ginzburg, C. and A. Shugaar, The Judge and the Historian, 1999Ginzburg, C., History, Rhetoric, and Proof, 1999.Ginzburg, C., No Island Is an Island, 2000.Ginzburg, C., Wooden Eyes: Nine Reflections on Distance, 2002.  VI. Theory, History and Criticism    理論，歷史與批評        Maharaj, Jayant, and Peter Manning, “Aesthetics and Architectural Criticism”, AAO, Vol.11, No.4, Fall 1979, pp.49-55.        Zevi, Bruno, “The Role of Critic of Architecture”, AAO, Vol.11, No.4, Fall 1979, pp.56-7.        Dickens, Peter, “The Hut and the Machine:  Towards a Social Theory of Architecture”, Architectural Design, No.1/2, 1981, pp.18-24.------------------------        Ockman, Joan et al., eds. Architecture Criticism Ideology, 1985.        Ockman, Joan et al., eds. Architectureproduction, Princeton, New Jersey: Princeton Architectural Press, 1988.MacLeod, Mary, “On Criticism”, Places, Vol.4, No.1, 1987, pp.4-6.------------------------Arnold, Dana, Reading Architectural History, London: Routledge 2002.Borden, Iain, and David Kunster, eds. Architecture and the Sites of History: Interpretations of Buildings and Cities, New York: Whitney Library of Design, 1995Borden, Iain, et al. eds. Strangely Familiar: Narratives of Architecture in the City, 1996.        Miles, Malcoln, Tim Hall and Iain Borden, eds. The City Cultures Reader, London: Routledge, 2000.        Rendell, Jane, Barbara Penner and Iain Borden, eds. Gender Space Architecture: An Interdisciplinary Introduction, London: Routledge, 2000.        Borden, Ian, Joe Kerr, Jane Rendell, with Alicia Pivaro, eds. The Unknown City: Contesting Architecture and Social Space, Cambridge, Massachusetts: The MIT Press, 2001.        Borden, Iain, and Jane Rendell, Intersections: Architectural Histories and Critical Theories, London: Routledge, 2000.註意：史學、文化研究與社會理論間近年的互動與新趨勢。        鄭時齡，2001，《建築批評學》，北京：中國建築工業出版社。










        
             
            

